PREFILED NOVEMBER 19, 2024
____________
Referred to Committee on Health and Human Services
SUMMARY—Revises provisions governing the adoption of
regulations for the administration of certain
programs of public assistance. (BDR 38-289)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: No.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to the public welfare; revising requirements
governing notice of the intent to adopt, amend or repeal
certain regulations or policies; authorizing the retroactive
application of certain regulations or policies; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Administrator of the Division of Health Care
2 Financing and Policy of the Department of Health and Human Services to provide
3 at least 30 days’ notice before adopting, amending or repealing any regulation for
4 the administration of a program of public assistance or other program for which the
5 Division is responsible. (NRS 422.2369) This bill authorizes the Administrator to
6 adopt, amend or repeal a regulation or policy with 3 business days’ notice if the
7 intended action: (1) is required to ensure compliance with federal or state law; or
8 (2) will result in an expansion of services or benefits. This bill additionally
9 authorizes the Administrator to adopt a regulation or policy, or an amendment or
10 repeal of a prior regulation or policy, that applies retroactively if such retroactivity
11 is necessary to ensure compliance with federal or state law and is clearly stated in
12 the regulation or policy, or the amendment or repeal of a prior regulation or policy.
